{"id":861,"category_slug":"ielts-listening","category_name":"IELTS Listening","position":223,"title":"Cam7 - Test 4 - Part 3","subtitle":"Planning an Education Presentation","level":"B1","parts":65,"url":"https://dailydictation.com/exercises/ielts-listening/cam7-test-4-part-3.861/listen-and-type","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-3-2023-07-31-19-32-33/0-ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-3.mp3","transcript":"Remind me, Trevor, how long is the presentation?\nDr White said three per hour.\nSo about twenty minutes?\nWell... it'll be fifteen minutes per presentation.\nAnd five minutes for questions.\nAnd is this one going to be assessed?\nNo, not this time round\nbecause it's the first one... you know.\nOh, good news.\nWell, Trevor, what are we going to include?\nWell, do you think we ought to give some historical background?\nOh no, definitely not, we won't have time!\nOK...\nbut I think we ought to say something about the geographical location\ncos not a lot of people know where the islands are.\nYes, okay...\nI'll take notes, shall I?\nYeah, that'll be a help.\nSo, geographical location...\nThen we ought to give an overview of the whole education system.\nShouldn't we say something about the economy,\nyou know agricultural produce, minerals and so forth?\nWell, Dr White said we shouldn't go into that sort of detail.\nBut it's pretty important when you think about it,\nyou know, because it does influence the education system.\nLook, let's think about that one later shall we?\nLet's see how we're doing for time.\nOkay, so... general overview of education.\nOf course... and then the role of English language.\nHmm... Nope, that goes in the Language Policy Seminar, don't you remember?\nAre you sure?\nPositive.\nAlright.\nso those are the topics we're going to be... to be covering.\nWe need to think about what to prepare...\nDr White said he wanted us to use plenty of visuals and things and...\nwe might as well try them out when we're not being assessed.\nWell, the most important thing is the overhead projector.\nNo problem, we'll get that from the media room.\nMust remember to book it.\nWell... we'll need a map of course.\nProbably two... one of the islands... large scale.\nAnd one of West Africa.\nWell, the West African one is no problem.\nThere's one in the Resources Room.\nOh yeah, of course, the resources room;\nthe islands are going to be more of a problem.\nTell you what, there's a very clear map of Santiago in that tourist brochure I showed you last week.\nDon't you remember it?\nOh yeah, that's right;\nwe can just use the tourist brochure.\nWe also need statistics on several different things.\nLiteracy rates.\nYes, and school places.\nHow about the encyclopedia?\nNah... not up-to-date enough!\nMmm... why don't we call the embassy?\nOh... someone's enthusiastic!\nWell... if something's worth doing...\nI know... it's worth doing well... okay.\nWe can find out statistics on school places from them as well.\nMight as well.\nLook, Julie, it's almost time for our tutorials.\nWe can meet again on Monday\nbut we need to prepare...","youtube_video_id":"","details_cached_at":"2026-06-15T20:51:21","challenges":[{"position":1,"content":"Remind me, Trevor, how long is the presentation?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-3-2023-07-31-19-32-33/1.mp3","time_start":0.45,"time_end":3.37},{"position":2,"content":"Dr White said three per hour.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-3-2023-07-31-19-32-33/2.mp3","time_start":3.37,"time_end":5.82},{"position":3,"content":"So about twenty minutes?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-3-2023-07-31-19-32-33/3.mp3","time_start":5.82,"time_end":7.82},{"position":4,"content":"Well... it'll be fifteen minutes per presentation.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-3-2023-07-31-19-32-33/4.mp3","time_start":7.82,"time_end":10.83},{"position":5,"content":"And five minutes for questions.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-3-2023-07-31-19-32-33/5.mp3","time_start":10.83,"time_end":12.93},{"position":6,"content":"And is this one going to be assessed?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-3-2023-07-31-19-32-33/6.mp3","time_start":13.19,"time_end":15.54},{"position":7,"content":"No, not this time round","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-3-2023-07-31-19-32-33/7.mp3","time_start":15.54,"time_end":17.53},{"position":8,"content":"because it's the first one... you know.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-3-2023-07-31-19-32-33/8.mp3","time_start":17.53,"time_end":19.62},{"position":9,"content":"Oh, good news.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-3-2023-07-31-19-32-33/9.mp3","time_start":19.62,"time_end":21.14},{"position":10,"content":"Well, Trevor, what are we going to include?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-3-2023-07-31-19-32-33/10.mp3","time_start":21.39,"time_end":24.27},{"position":11,"content":"Well, do you think we ought to give some historical background?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-3-2023-07-31-19-32-33/11.mp3","time_start":24.27,"time_end":27.97},{"position":12,"content":"Oh no, definitely not, we won't have time!","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-3-2023-07-31-19-32-33/12.mp3","time_start":27.97,"time_end":30.86},{"position":13,"content":"OK...","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-